 us leadership customer testimonials careers finance products transportation equipment leaseloan products leasepurchase program financing industries served customers manufacturers and dealers fleets  owneroperators industrial equipment manufacturing machine tool financing fabrication woodworking plastics printing packaging and processing tax benefits – section  construction equipment invoice factoring syndications offlease equipment insurance products and services insurance faqs contact engs insurance agency blog industry news help contact us customer service center dealer login financing your first big rigengs commercial finance  blog  financing your first big rig may   engs commercial financeblog comment you’re probably familiar with the process you walk into your local car dealership peruse the lot and are pounced on by an eager salesperson  after a bit of chitchat you take the car out for a test drive pop the hood and you might even do some quick research online on your phone to see if you’re getting a deal or the right packages with the car  a bit of haggling later you shake hands and start signing papers  if you’re financing the car you can use the inhouse lender or go back to your bank and get a loan for the balance less deposit andor tradein  easy right semi truck purchases are quite different from buying a sedan from your local dealer most definitely when it comes to financing the purchase  big rig financing falls somewhere between a business loan and vehicle loan and most banks don’t deal with truck loans or aren’t equipped to appropriately determine terms and payments  many semi truck dealers have preferred vendors inhouse who can provide funding however you want to be sure you’re signing up with a financing company and payment terms that work for your business choose a truck financing specialist it’s true not every big bank in town will fund semi truck purchases however there are a number of commercial finance companies who specialize in funding truck loans and leases  a trucking industry loan specialist understands more about your industry than simply a credit score and asset depreciation which are certainly important but also is familiar with the type of equipment you’re purchases load types certain restrictions and seasonal and economic influences that will impact your ability to pay  you’re not simply choosing a truck finance company—you’re choosing a strategic financing partner for your business understand your creditworthiness just like any other loan a truck financier will look at the purchaser’s credit history and score which will influence borrowing limit rate and terms on a repayment schedule  if you walk into the lending office or phone call with this information you’ll be prepared to have a more direct conversation with your potential lender often leading to either better rates more tailored payment schedule or possibly both  at the end of the day you’re looking to be behind the wheel hauling loads and earning money  picking a strategic lending partner up front can put you in the cab faster and keep you there for the road ahead one thought on “financing your first big rig” i really like that you touch on how important it is to understand how a lender will view you it makes sense that your credit score history etc will all have an effect on how a lender views you as loan worthy this could be particularly helpful to understand for such a large loan like for a big rig because it can be a very delicate situation reply leave a reply cancel reply your email address will not be published required fields are marked comment name  email  website recent posts tips for working with a load broker how to purchase a big rig engs commercial capital closes on a mm factoring facility is short haul trucking for me the owner operator’s dilemma how to choose the right trucking company recent commentstyler on financing your first big rigtyler meredith on  tips for growing businessesanna jones on how small machine shops gain 