ows shows that music at roughly  beats per minute bpm will allow your brainwaves to subconsciously synchronize with the music getting you into a calming rhythm without putting you to sleep  a simple yet effective way to take the edge off of a stressful route know your route often we’re asked to make new deliveries sometimes in areas we’re unfamiliar with  take a few minutes with a map ahead of time to identify the potentially troublesome areas and make mental or paper notes of landmarks or cross streets leading up to an important intersection in the age of the smartphone and gps it doesn’t hurt to set up the destination in your device but do note that sometimes road closures construction or redevelopment may be different than the latest map update in your device  it doesn’t hurt to also have mental notes of roads in the region as previously mentioned stay hydrated to combat stress many of us drink coffee or tea when we get up to get a caffeine jolt and when available we consume various forms of caffeine throughout the day  instead try starting your day with caffeine to get you moving but shift to water or a lowcalorie hydration drink  drinking water hydrates your organs including the brain helping it function optimally which in turn studies have shown decreases the concentration and production of cortisol the stress hormone  drinking water has numerous health benefits beyond coping with stress and the only down side is maybe a few more pit stops along the way—a welcome break to stretch picking the right partners a significant stressor for any business owner is finances  we want more than to simply keep the doors open we want to grow and thrive  with trucking a sizable portion of expense goes into our equipment and funding the purchase or lease of a new truck can be overwhelming  another way to beat stress as a trucker is to choose a truck and trailer financing company who knows the industry and is in your corner providing sensible financing options that will help you acquire the equipment you need to grow your business leave a reply cancel reply your email address will not be published required fields are marked comment name  email  website recent posts tips for working with a load broker how to purchase a big rig engs commercial capital closes on a mm factoring facility is short haul trucking for me the owner operator’s dilemma how to choose the right trucking company recent commentstyler on financing your first big rigtyler meredith on  tips for growing businessesanna jones on how small machine shops gain competitive edgezachary tomlinson on be prepared trucking insurance for on and off dispatchemily bennette on how small machine shops gain competitive edgearchives july  june  may  april  march  february  january  december  november  october  september  august  july  june  may  april  march  february  january  june  april  february  december  november  october  september  august  july  june  categories act research blog company news factoring releases press releases meta log in entries rss comments rss wordpressorg copyright   engs commercial finance •    privacy policy design  seo by nathan wiens consulting llc